tv.amwa.maj.io.mxf

Annotation Type MXFLength


  • @Documented
 @Target(value={FIELD,PARAMETER,METHOD})
public @interface MXFLength

    Labels a value that represents the length of an item in an MXF file, measured in bytes. Values are 64 bit signed integers represented as Java long values.

    Note that this is different from a LengthType which is a value that represents the length of an AAF component measured in edit units rather than the number of bytes taken up by an item in an AAF file.

    See Also:
    Int64, LengthType, MXFPosition
